Pairwise Comparison

pairs(var, pch = 20)

ggcorr(data = var, label = TRUE, label_size = 2, hjust = 0.8)
## Warning in ggcorr(data = var, label = TRUE, label_size = 2, hjust = 0.8): data
## in column(s) 'state' are not numeric and were ignored

From the correlation plot, we can see there are terms with high correlation: Number of active physicians & Number of hospital beds; Number of hospital beds & Total personal income; Number of active physicians & Total personal income; Total population & Number of active physicians; Total population & Number of hospital beds; Total population & Total personal Income

Interaction Terms

Include interaction terms of highly correlated variables into the dataset.

with_inter = var %>% 
  mutate(
    docs_beds = docs*beds,
    beds_totalinc = beds*totalinc,
    docs_totalinc = docs*totalinc,
    pop_docs = pop*docs,
    pop_beds = pop*beds,
    pop_totalinc = pop*totalinc
    )
